I keep thinking I should make a SoFurry writer's guide. For now I'll post some basic tips and the reasoning.


>useful tags on SoFurry all hmofa writers should be using:
M/F
Human
Male
>whatever species the waifur is i.e. Wolf
Female

>the unofficial tag:
hmofa

Using those tags first helps people immediately know you've got a story aimed at straight people and it involves a human paramour. It also helps people searching for stories like yours. There is most certainly a portion of readers there interested in hmofa content that don't like 4chan, but if you don't get some essential tags in you will be passed over.

Greentext generally doesn't do as well as prose there but it's not off putting.

Don't treat SF like pastebin (this goes for Ao3 as well). When you upload a new update do it as a new chapter, not an edit to an existing submission. A story submission that's too long will lag or crash the webpage because SF is using janky 2009 programming, as Oliver discovered and as you can see when going to look at Mechanized Memories on SF.
